cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SI, cs.CV 

The paper proposes a machine learning model for online incremental clustering, which falls under the category of unsupervised learning. The model uses a neural network architecture and activation function, which suggests it could belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of distance and intersection over union (IoU) criteria, which are commonly used in computer vision and image processing, indicating a possible connection to cs.CV (Computer Vision). The use of a node grouping algorithm and vigilance parameters suggests a possible connection to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
